<Class name="CM_YAParser" id="918c7f0e-7353-4fc5-ae72-32551a09d25a">
    <superclass name="CM_YardAllocationItem"/>
    <transient/>
    <sharedTransientAllowed/>
    <subclassSharedTransientAllowed/>
    <subclassTransientAllowed/>
    <transientAllowed/>
    <access>protected</access>
    <text>Use transient instances of this class to parse a user input string or Yard Allocation
locations, and to maintain an array of YA Blocks for the parsed locations.

The Location ID entered by the user should be formatted into tokens that are separated
by a space, as per the following:

	&lt;area&gt; &lt;row&gt;&lt;column&gt;

...this may take various be formats, such as:

	A (and area only, i.e. take the whole area)
	A 02 (row only, i.e. take the whole row)
	A 01-03 (a range of three rows)
	A 0205 (a single cell)
	A 0201,0205,0508 (a list of cells)
	A 0101-0210 (a range of cells)
	A 0102,0107,0203,0207-0210; B 0207,0305 (various combinations of areas, lists and ranges)

To use this class, follow these steps:

1) Instantiate the class;

2) Call the "loadBlocks" method, to populate the parser with any existing Blocks.

3) Call the "parseLocationsString" method, sending the user input string to it.  The method
will return a boolean value to indicate the success of the parser.  It the parser failed,
the read only property "errorMessage" will contain an explanation for the failure (assuming
there was not an exception).

If the parser was successful, the array property "allYABlocks" will have been populated
with the neccessary Yard Allocation Blocks for all of the locations.</text>
    <DbClassMap file="cmtrans"/>
    <Constant name="VALID_CHARS" id="576a4a0c-c9bf-453e-9294-a10d9ecf4cd6">
        <source>"abcdefghijklmnopqrstuvwxyzABCDEFGHIJKLMNOPQRSTUVWXYZ0123456789 ;,-&amp;/\_&lt;&gt;:"</source>
        <type name="String"/>
    </Constant>
